<chapter xml:id="ch_waves" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Waves</title>
	<introduction>
    <p>In this chapter, you will build a model for waves.</p>
	
	<p><alert>Learning Outcomes</alert></p>
  
  
<p> After successful completion of this chapter, you will be able to:
 <ol>
<li>Define a wave</li>
<li>Define wave properties like period, frequency, wavelength, wave number, and amplitude</li>
<li>Identify wave properties using graphical analysis</li>
<li>Describe how the wave speed changes when the medium through which the wave is travelling changes</li>
<li>Use superposition to understand how waves interfere with each other</li>
<li>Describe what happens when a wave hits a boundary that is fixed or free</li>
<li>Define path length difference</li>
<li>Define maximum constructive and destructive interference</li>
<li>Analyze the path length difference of a system to determine the type of interference seen</li>
<li>Define standing waves</li>
<li>Define intensity</li>
<li>Define loudness</li>
<li>Define the Dopper Effect</li>

<li></li>
</ol>

</p>

